Author: bishop#9773
Content: So how does the rewards calc work with rewards prior to block 1M. For instance, if I had funds that haven't claimed rewards on since a month prior, do they accrue all of September or what?

Author: bishop#9773
Content: just curious how the one month calc is done

Author: Hermes#6934
Content: The rule consists now that you will need to do it once a month , if you claimed a month ago and you claim for instance today it will be the same as before

Author: Hermes#6934
Content: just that from now on is obligatory to claim monthly.

Author: bishop#9773
Content: And I get that, but in my situation, if I didn't claim today, does it accrue to the end of September or does it cap out? I only ask because in this situation, I would be over the one month mark but with the block change, no idea

Author: Hermes#6934
Content: If you had past rewards before the network rules change you could have claimed then now,  but if you are asking if that rule is retroactive like if that will take in account the last time you did before block  1 mm it won't make too much sense because the rule has just been applied from the block 1 mm and beyond

Author: bishop#9773
Content: I'm just asking if anyone that didn't claim prior to block 1M is accuring rewards or if they stop toward the end of september/early october

Author: bishop#9773
Content: did rewards stop the second block 1M happened I guess is the simpliest

Author: Hermes#6934
Content: I still accrued rewards that were previous the 1 mm change and we also tested it , we claimed the rewards just after the 1 mm block and one hour later we claimed them again.

Author: bishop#9773
Content: so in that situation, it sounds like they will accrue through september, no?

Author: bishop#9773
Content: then cap out

Author: bishop#9773
Content: Don't get me wrong, I already claim once a month (sometimes twice) but more or less curious if I have until the end of the month or if unclaimed at block 1M is capped

Author: bishop#9773
Content: just haven't seen anything clear regarding it

Author: Hermes#6934
Content: Yes , it's a good question although block 1 mm was on the 7th of Sept in the night , will keep you posted to clarify this

Author: bishop#9773
Content: Yep, I was around when it happened. More curiosity than anything

Author: bishop#9773
Content: Thanks!

Author: Alright#0419
Content: @bishop UTXOs that were created prior to block 1M won't cap for a year

Author: Alright#0419
Content: is that what you're asking?

Author: bishop#9773
Content: Perfect, thank you @Alright
